<script type="text/javascript">
function togPhase(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + n);
	e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
}
function togAllPhases(display) {
	for (var i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
		var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + i);
		if (!e) break;
		e.style.display = display;
	}
}
function addHint(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phase');
	for (var i = 0; i < e.childNodes.length; i++) {
		e.childNodes[i].selected = e.childNodes[i].value == n ? 'selected' : '';
	}
	e = document.getElementById('text');
	e.focus();
	e.select();
}
</script>

<div class="mm white">
This quest <span class="blue">[<span class="yellow">801</span>]</span> is called '<span class="yellow">Grounds for a Lawsuit</span>',<br/>
for Adventurers levels <span class="yellow">180</span> to <span class="yellow">241</span>.<br />


<span class="hg"><a href="/npc/647">Lord Agrippa</a> [<a href="/area/48">Runic Castle</a>] is the master in charge of this quest.</span><br />

A dear friend of mine has fallen ill and I believe it is because of a cup<br />
of coffee he drank two nights ago was more than just the coffee he thought<br />
he was being served.  Apparently it was tainted with human blood, a most<br />
revolting thought!  He apparently had a severe allergic reaction to the<br />
blood or some other substance that was in the coffee.  Unfortunately, the<br />
attorney cannot prosecute locally, because the exporter of the drink resides<br />
in Xaventry.  Please gather evidence and take it to sympathetic lawyers<br />
there to see if the case can be taken to trial.  I would hate to see anyone<br />
else have the trouble my friend has had because of tainted coffee!  Hurry<br />
back with a report of your findings and you will be well rewarded.  <br />

<span class="hy">Upon successful completion of this quest you can receive:</span><br />

<span class="hm">*</span>Up to <span class="yellow">60</span> quest points, <span class="yellow">6</span> practice points, <span class="yellow">30,000</span> experience points,<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="yellow">0</span> build points, <span class="yellow">0</span> piety, and <span class="yellow">7,500</span> gold pieces.<br />


You have <span class="yellow">300</span> minutes remaining to complete this quest.<br />

Grounds for a Lawsuit consists of:<br />


	<div class="phase" id="phase1">


		<a class="hints" href="javascript:togPhase(1);">Phase 1</a>: Locate and deliver <a href="/item/1598">a jug of caffeinated blood</a> to <a href="/npc/1566">The attorney general</a>. 		
		<div class="phasehints" id="phasehint1" style="display: none;">

<div class="phaseinfoitem">from <a href="/npc/468">Alimenta</a> (shop #1) [<a href="/room/3316/">Alimenta's Tavern</a>, <a href="/area/45" class="white">Rahdiyr</a>],<br /><a href="/npc/3443">Faith</a> (shop #1) [<a href="/room/305/">The Dancing Faerie</a>, <a href="/area/61" class="white">The Towne of New Rigel</a>],<br /><a href="/npc/970">A resting guard</a>  [<a href="/area/70" class="white">Unseelie Castle</a>],<br /><a href="/npc/5215">A smirking drow bartender</a> (shop #1) [<a href="/area/156" class="white">Xalt, Unseelie Outpost</a>].</div><div class="phaseinfomob">in <a href="/room/10860">The Prosecution's Podium</a>, <a href="/area/75">The Towne of Xaventry</a>.</div>


			<div class="phasehint">
				A jug of caffeinated blood can be bought from the Dancing Faerie in New Rigel, The Attorney General is in Xaventry in the courtroom				&mdash;
				Phae							</div>


			<div class="phasehint">
				The resting guard from Phase 3 also carries these.				&mdash;
				Cyrekim							</div>


		</div>
	</div>


	<div class="phase" id="phase2">


		<a class="hints" href="javascript:togPhase(2);">Phase 2</a>: Locate and deliver <a href="/item/2041">a cup of coffee</a> to <a href="/npc/1341">Judge Sherwood</a>. 		
		<div class="phasehints" id="phasehint2" style="display: none;">

<div class="phaseinfoitem">from <a href="/npc/4996">A drunken elf gambler</a> (shop #12) [<a href="/area/105" class="white">Emperor's Crossroads</a>],<br /><a href="/npc/4952">Teril Amada, the Innkeeper</a> (shop #12) [<a href="/room/25272/">Northern End of the Common Room</a>, <a href="/area/105" class="white">Emperor's Crossroads</a>],<br /><a href="/npc/65">Artur, King of Kona</a> (shop #12) [<a href="/room/5145/">Artur's Coffee and Cakes</a>, <a href="/area/51" class="white">Sigil</a>],<br /><a href="/npc/3275">A serving girl</a>  [<a href="/area/19" class="white">The Lonely Dragon Inn</a>],<br /><a href="/npc/3284">A serving girl</a>  [<a href="/area/19" class="white">The Lonely Dragon Inn</a>],<br /><a href="/npc/3318">A serving girl</a>  [<a href="/area/19" class="white">The Lonely Dragon Inn</a>].</div><div class="phaseinfomob">in <a href="/room/10858">Judge Sherwood's Desk</a>, <a href="/area/75">The Towne of Xaventry</a>.</div>


			<div class="phasehint">
				A cup of Coffee can be bought in the Lonely Dragon Inn from the serving girl. Judge Sherwood is in the courtroom in Xaventry.				&mdash;
				Phae							</div>


		</div>
	</div>


